{
 "name": "RPlog_Unexpected_Conversations",
 "title": "Unexpected Conversations: A Reckoning in the Sandbar",
 "summary": "In Caspar's Sandbar, the exiled former Imperial doctor Lynae Caiton--kept alive on borrowed time by a rewired pacemaker implanted as punishment for her treason--confronts her hard-drinking friend Keifan over his slide toward the Maffi underworld and andriss addiction, drawing the wary attention of the local pilot Jamon. When the argument spikes her sabotaged heart and she collapses, Keifan, a former Imperial himself, revives her, and the wandering Jedi Johanna arrives to offer Lynae a fresh start traveling at her side. The fragile peace fractures as Darth Malign, the criminal Malif, the mercenaries Dareus and Axel, the marine Webb, and finally the CDU President Mahon and his guards filter into the bar; Malign baits and threatens Lynae, who defiantly defends free will and the Caspian way before Mahon declares the Sith persona non grata. At last the healer Brandis Finian--whom Lynae once helped torture--arrives at her summons, and after a tense negotiation she swears him a future favor in exchange for his aid, and he Force-heals her damaged heart enough to buy time for the surgery that may finally free her from the device.",
